history.content: Try and see if you can take it concurrently with DS 100, or at least review the Data 8 textbook before the class. I'm currently in DS 100, and I've noticed students who have not taken Data 8 have found some of the concepts difficult to understand (in particular, concepts introduced in Data 8 such as bootstrapping). I suggest you either take the class (imo, do this) or review the Data 8 textbook, especially if you haven't taken a statistics class before.

children.subject: May I know what is the workload of the class compared to the 61 series? I wish to take the class with CS 61B and I have also taken stats in high school.
Its slightly more than 61A but definitely less than 61B. I'd say 1.5x 61A workload.

I am in ds100 now, without taking Data 8. I took high school AP stats. I have had a great time in the class, and there haven't been any topics that I can recall feeling behind on or feeling like I was expected to know coming in. Before taking the class though, I skimmed the Data 8 syllabus and saw that most of the stuff I had heard of before or could figure out on the fly, so you should definitely take a look at that. (Your experiences may vary though)
